#. (itstool) path: sect1/title
#: xml/update_split_brain.xml:18
msgid "The Atomic Update"
msgstr "The Atomic Update"

#. (itstool) path: sect1/para
#: xml/update_split_brain.xml:26
msgid ""
"The Atomic Update is based on tools that manage two copies of the system and "
"allow easy recovery after an update failure. The delivered tools require a "
"special disk partition setup. Every copy of the system resides on a primary "
"partition of its own. If an update fails, you can always switch back to the "
"previous state of the system, which is available on the other partition."
msgstr ""
"The Atomic Update is based on tools that manage two copies of the system and "
"allow easy recovery after an update failure. The delivered tools require a "
"special disk partition setup. Every copy of the system resides on a primary "
"partition of its own. If an update fails, you can always switch back to the "
"previous state of the system, which is available on the other partition."

